# MetaMask Design System - Layout & Spacing

This document defines the official spacing and border radius tokens for the MetaMask design system. All components must use these values for consistent layout.

## Usage

Always use design tokens for spacing and border radius. Never use raw pixel values directly.

```tsx
import { spacing, radius } from "@/lib/tokens";

// ✅ Correct
style={{ padding: spacing[4] }}
style={{ borderRadius: radius.lg }}
style={{ gap: spacing[2] }}

// ❌ Incorrect
style={{ padding: 16 }}
style={{ borderRadius: 12 }}
style={{ gap: 8 }}
```

## Spacing Scale

Based on a 4px unit system:

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `spacing[1]` | 4px | Tight gaps between inline elements, icon margins |
| `spacing[2]` | 8px | Small gaps, badge padding, button groups |
| `spacing[3]` | 12px | Medium gaps, list item vertical padding |
| `spacing[4]` | 16px | Standard padding, cell padding, section gaps |
| `spacing[5]` | 20px | Medium-large gaps |
| `spacing[6]` | 24px | Card padding, section spacing |
| `spacing[8]` | 32px | Large section gaps, page margins |
| `spacing[10]` | 40px | Extra large gaps |
| `spacing[12]` | 48px | Major section dividers |

### Common Spacing Patterns

| Context | Token | Example |
|---------|-------|---------|
| Card internal padding | `spacing[6]` | `padding: spacing[6]` |
| List item padding | `spacing[4]` | `padding: spacing[4]` |
| Gap between buttons | `spacing[2]` | `gap: spacing[2]` |
| Gap between list items | `spacing[2]` | `gap: spacing[2]` |
| Icon to text gap | `spacing[2]` | `gap: spacing[2]` |
| Badge internal padding | `spacing[1]` / `spacing[2]` | `padding: \`\${spacing[1]}px \${spacing[2]}px\`` |
| Section title to content | `spacing[4]` | `marginBottom: spacing[4]` |

## Border Radius Scale

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `radius.xs` | 4px | Small elements, tags |
| `radius.sm` | 8px | Buttons, inputs, small cards |
| `radius.md` | 12px | Medium cards, dialogs |
| `radius.lg` | 16px | Large cards, containers |
| `radius.xl` | 24px | Modals, drawers (top corners) |
| `radius.full` | 9999px | Avatars, pills, circular buttons |

### Common Radius Patterns

| Element Type | Token | Example |
|--------------|-------|---------|
| Buttons | `radius.sm` | `borderRadius: radius.sm` |
| Input fields | `radius.sm` | `borderRadius: radius.sm` |
| Cards | `radius.lg` | `borderRadius: radius.lg` |
| Token cells | `radius.lg` | `borderRadius: radius.lg` |
| Modals/Dialogs | `radius.xl` | `borderRadius: radius.xl` |
| Drawers | `radius.xl` (top only) | `borderRadius: \`\${radius.xl}px \${radius.xl}px 0 0\`` |
| Avatars | `radius.full` | `borderRadius: radius.full` |
| Badges/Pills | `radius.full` | `borderRadius: radius.full` |

## Layout Guidelines

### Containers

```tsx
// Card container
style={{
  padding: spacing[6],
  borderRadius: radius.lg,
  backgroundColor: c.background.section,
}}

// Nested container  
style={{
  padding: spacing[4],
  borderRadius: radius.md,
  backgroundColor: c.background.subsection,
}}
```

### Lists

```tsx
// List container
style={{
  display: "flex",
  flexDirection: "column",
  gap: spacing[1], // Tight gaps between items
}}

// List item
style={{
  padding: `${spacing[3]}px ${spacing[4]}px`,
  borderRadius: radius.lg,
}}
```

### Forms

```tsx
// Form container
style={{
  display: "flex",
  flexDirection: "column",
  gap: spacing[4], // Gap between fields
}}

// Label + Input group
style={{
  display: "flex",
  flexDirection: "column",
  gap: spacing[2], // Gap between label and input
}}

// Input field
style={{
  padding: `${spacing[3]}px ${spacing[4]}px`,
  borderRadius: radius.sm,
}}
```

### Buttons

```tsx
// Standard button
style={{
  padding: `${spacing[3]}px ${spacing[4]}px`,
  borderRadius: radius.sm,
}}

// Button group
style={{
  display: "flex",
  gap: spacing[2],
}}

// Icon button
style={{
  width: 40,
  height: 40,
  borderRadius: radius.full,
}}
```

### Headers

```tsx
// Section header
style={{
  display: "flex",
  alignItems: "center",
  justifyContent: "space-between",
  marginBottom: spacing[4],
}}

// Page header
style={{
  padding: spacing[4],
  paddingTop: spacing[2],
}}
```

## Mobile App Dimensions

Standard mobile viewport:
- Width: 375px (iPhone standard)
- Full height with safe areas

```tsx
// Mobile container
style={{
  width: "100%",
  maxWidth: 375,
  minHeight: "100vh",
}}

// Safe area padding (approximate)
const safeArea = {
  top: 47,    // Status bar + notch
  bottom: 34, // Home indicator
};
```

